
                                                        +-------+
                                                        |  .TY  |
                                                        +-------+

TYPE displays a line of information at the terminal.

     +-------+---------------------------------------------+
     |       |                                             |
     |  .TY  |    information                              |
     |       |                                             |
     +-------+---------------------------------------------+

This control word does not cause a break.   If used with no oper-
ands, a blank line is displayed.   The text of the line displayed
is  modified by  the  .TR  (Translate)  characters  currently  in
effect.

<.U+>EXAMPLES<.NORMAL>
(1) The  .TY  control  is  useful  immediately  preceding  a  .TE
    (Terminal Input)  or .RV (Read Variable)  control word,  as a
    prompt for what to type in response:
    .ty Type Name and Address in five lines or less:
    .te 5
(2) .ty Specify number of output columns:
    .rv ncols
    .cd set &ncols

